main event: A bright object was observed stationary at 15 degrees elevation for 10 minutes near Vandenberg radar site in Lompoc, California.
interesting points: The object appeared to be over the Vandenberg radar site.
Local radar site could not locate the object 30 minutes later.
The description of the object indicates a possible launching observation.
There was no report of a UFO from Vandenberg Air Force Base.
The object was likely a launch from Vandenberg Air Force Base or other local balloon launching activity.
result: probable launch from Vandenberg Air Force Base or other local balloon launching activity
sighted object: one bright object, egg-shaped, nickel in color, approximately 5 feet in size, with no sound
